<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="C33.S6">
<title>Power-Series Expansions in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.m1">\rho</Math></title>        
  
<para xml:id="C33.S6.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C33.S6.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="33.6.1" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S6.E1">F_{\ell}\left(\eta,\rho\right)=C_{\ell}\left(\eta\right)\sum_{k=\ell+1}^{ \infty}A_{k}^{\ell}(\eta)\rho^{k},</Math> <Math equation-number="33.6.2" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S6.E2">F_{\ell}'\left(\eta,\rho\right)=C_{\ell}\left(\eta\right)\sum_{k=\ell+1}^{ \infty}kA_{k}^{\ell}(\eta)\rho^{k-1},</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p1.m1">A_{\ell+1}^{\ell}=1</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p1.m2">A_{\ell+2}^{\ell}=\eta/(\ell+1)</Math> , and <Math equation-number="33.6.3" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S6.E3">(k+\ell)(k-\ell-1)A_{k}^{\ell}=2\eta A_{k-1}^{\ell}-A_{k-2}^{\ell}, if k=\ell+3,\ell+4,\dots,</Math> or in terms of the hypergeometric function (§§15.1,15.2(i)),
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C33.S6.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="33.6.4" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S6.E4">A_{k}^{\ell}(\eta)=\dfrac{(-\mathrm{i})^{k-\ell-1}}{(k-\ell-1)!}\*{{}_{2}F_{1} }\left(\ell+1-k,\ell+1-\mathrm{i}\eta;2\ell+2;2\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C33.S6.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C33.S6.p2.s1">
 <Math equation-number="33.6.5" mode="display" xml:id="C33.S6.E5">{H^{\pm}_{\ell}}\left(\eta,\rho\right)=\frac{e^{\pm\mathrm{i}{\theta_{\ell}} \left(\eta,\rho\right)}}{(2\ell+1)!\Gamma\left(-\ell\pm\mathrm{i}\eta\right)} \left(\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{{\left(a\right)_{k}}}{{\left(2\ell+2\right)_{k} }k!}(\mp 2\mathrm{i}\rho)^{a+k}\left(\ln\left(\mp 2\mathrm{i}\rho\right)+\psi \left(a+k\right)-\psi\left(1+k\right)-\psi\left(2\ell+2+k\right)\right)-\sum_{ k=1}^{2\ell+1}\frac{(2\ell+1)!(k-1)!}{(2\ell+1-k)!{\left(1-a\right)_{k}}}(\mp 2 \mathrm{i}\rho)^{a-k}\right),</Math> 
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C33.S6.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C33.S6.p3.s1">
where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p3.m1">a=1+\ell\pm\mathrm{i}\eta</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p3.m2">\psi\left(x\right)=\Gamma'\left(x\right)/\Gamma\left(x\right)</Math> (§5.2(i)).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C33.S6.p4">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C33.S6.p4.s1">
The series (33.6.1),(33.6.2),and(33.6.5)converge for all finite values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p4.m1">\rho</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C33.S6.p4.s2">
Corresponding expansions for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C33.S6.p4.m2">{H^{\pm}_{\ell}}'\left(\eta,\rho\right)</Math> can be obtained by combining (33.6.5) with (33.4.3) or (33.4.4).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</section>
